        <div class="devsite-landing-row-item-description"
         >

      

      <div class="devsite-landing-row-item-body">
        
                    <h3 id="design-for-seamless-connectivity">
      Design for seamless connectivity</h3>
    
    

                  <div class="devsite-landing-row-item-description-content">
            Low bandwidth and intermittent connectivity are the norm for many people accessing the web. Most people online still have 2G connections or "3G" that downgrades to 2G. Even by 2020, more than 10% of users will still be on 2G. Many smartphones are used offline, and users regularly turn on airplane mode to avoid data consumption.

          </div>
        
        
                  <div class="devsite-landing-row-item-buttons">
      <a href="/web/fundamentals/performance/poor-connectivity#testing"
      class="wf-small-link
      "
            >Test with emulated low bandwidth and high latency</a>    <a href="/web/fundamentals/performance/poor-connectivity#lie-fi"
      class="wf-small-link
      "
            >Handle unreliable connectivity and "lie-fi"</a>    <a href="/web/fundamentals/codelabs/offline"
      class="wf-small-link
      "
            >Design for offline</a>    <a href="/web/fundamentals/performance/optimizing-content-efficiency/eliminate-downloads"
      class="wf-small-link
      "
            >Reduce the number of resource requests</a>    <a href="/web/fundamentals/performance/optimizing-content-efficiency/optimize-encoding-and-transfer"
      class="wf-small-link
      "
            >Make installs and updates as small and fast as possible</a></div>
              </div>
    </div>
      
</div>
              <div class="devsite-landing-row-item"
     
     >

  
    <div class="devsite-landing-row-item-media
            ">
      <figure class="devsite-landing-row-item-image">
          <img alt=""
       src="https://developers.google.com/web/billions/images/cost.png"
       srcset="https://developers.google.com/web/billions/images/cost_36.png 36w,https://developers.google.com/web/billions/images/cost_48.png 48w,https://developers.google.com/web/billions/images/cost_72.png 72w,https://developers.google.com/web/billions/images/cost_96.png 96w,https://developers.google.com/web/billions/images/cost_480.png 480w,https://developers.google.com/web/billions/images/cost_720.png 720w,https://developers.google.com/web/billions/images/cost_856.png 856w,https://developers.google.com/web/billions/images/cost_960.png 960w,https://developers.google.com/web/billions/images/cost_1440.png 1440w,https://developers.google.com/web/billions/images/cost_1920.png 1920w,https://developers.google.com/web/billions/images/cost_2880.png 2880w"
       sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, (max-width: 840px) 50vw, 708px">
  
  </figure>
  </div>


        <div class="devsite-landing-row-item-description"
         >

      

      <div class="devsite-landing-row-item-body">
        
                    <h3 id="conserve-data-usage">
      Conserve data usage</h3>
    
    

                  <div class="devsite-landing-row-item-description-content">
            High data cost is often a greater barrier to access than poor connectivity. Mobile users are cost-conscious; even "unlimited" plans can become expensive when roaming or if unexpected fees are applied. Many mobile users are extremely cost conscious, with good reason: for example, a 500MB data plan in India costs the same as 17 hours of minimum wage work.

          </div>
        
        
                  <div class="devsite-landing-row-item-buttons">
      <a href="/web/fundamentals/design-and-ux/responsive/content#weight"
      class="wf-small-link
      "
            >Understand the cost of loading page and app components</a>    <a href="/web/fundamentals/performance/optimizing-content-efficiency"
      class="wf-small-link
      "
            >Reduce the amount of data required for interaction</a>    <a href="/web/fundamentals/design-and-ux/principles#home-page-and-site-navigation"
      class="wf-small-link
      "
            >Streamline navigation: help users get to what they want</a>    <a href="/web/fundamentals/performance/critical-rendering-path"
      class="wf-small-link
      "
            >Prioritize content display</a></div>
              </div>
    </div>
      
</div>
            </div>
    
  
  </section>
