       sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, (max-width: 840px) 50vw, 708px">
  
  </figure>
  </div>


        <div class="devsite-landing-row-item-description"
         >

      

      <div class="devsite-landing-row-item-body">
        
                    <h3 id="reduce-battery-consumption">
      Reduce battery consumption</h3>
    
    

                  <div class="devsite-landing-row-item-description-content">
            Many people, even in urban areas, don't have access to a reliable and affordable power supply. This makes power conservation a critical factor in all app and content design.

          </div>
        
        
                  <div class="devsite-landing-row-item-buttons">
      <a href="/web/tools/chrome-devtools/rendering-tools/forced-synchronous-layouts"
      class="wf-small-link
      "
            >Avoid repaints, reflows, and required reorientations</a>    <a href="/web/fundamentals/design-and-ux/animations#avoid-animating-expensive-properties/"
      class="wf-small-link
      "
            >Avoid expensive UI animations</a>    <a href="/web/fundamentals/performance/optimizing-content-efficiency/eliminate-downloads"
      class="wf-small-link
      "
            >Avoid radio usage: eliminate unnecessary downloads</a>    <a href="/web/fundamentals/design-and-ux/principles"
      class="wf-small-link
      "
            >Reduce user actions required to access content</a>    <a href="/web/fundamentals/design-and-ux/animations/animations-and-performance"
      class="wf-small-link
      "
            >Avoid expensive animations</a></div>
              </div>
    </div>
      
</div>
              <div class="devsite-landing-row-item"
     
     >

  
    <div class="devsite-landing-row-item-media
            ">
      <figure class="devsite-landing-row-item-image">
          <img alt=""
       src="https://developers.google.com/web/billions/images/capability.png"
       srcset="https://developers.google.com/web/billions/images/capability_36.png 36w,https://developers.google.com/web/billions/images/capability_48.png 48w,https://developers.google.com/web/billions/images/capability_72.png 72w,https://developers.google.com/web/billions/images/capability_96.png 96w,https://developers.google.com/web/billions/images/capability_480.png 480w,https://developers.google.com/web/billions/images/capability_720.png 720w,https://developers.google.com/web/billions/images/capability_856.png 856w,https://developers.google.com/web/billions/images/capability_960.png 960w,https://developers.google.com/web/billions/images/capability_1440.png 1440w,https://developers.google.com/web/billions/images/capability_1920.png 1920w,https://developers.google.com/web/billions/images/capability_2880.png 2880w"
       sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, (max-width: 840px) 50vw, 708px">
  
  </figure>
  </div>


        <div class="devsite-landing-row-item-description"
         >

      

      <div class="devsite-landing-row-item-body">
        
                    <h3 id="optimize-for-device-capability">
      Optimize for device capability</h3>
    
    

                  <div class="devsite-landing-row-item-description-content">
            Low spec is the norm. Globally, most new internet users have low-cost devices with basic hardware: single-core processors, 4" screens, limited memory, and limited storage.

          </div>
        
        
                  <div class="devsite-landing-row-item-buttons">
      <a href="/web/fundamentals/codelabs/your-first-multi-screen-site"
      class="wf-small-link
      "
            >Cater for a range of viewports and devices</a>    <a href="/web/fundamentals/performance"
      class="wf-small-link
      "
            >Design for limited memory and CPU: reduce and optimize</a></div>
              </div>
    </div>
      
</div>
            </div>
    
  
  </section>
