        <div class="devsite-landing-row-item-description"
         >

      

      <div class="devsite-landing-row-item-body">
        
                    <h3 id="build-multi-device-content">
      Build multi-device content</h3>
    
    

                  <div class="devsite-landing-row-item-description-content">
            Large-layout, graphics-heavy content frustrates users and discourages them from using your app or site. Content that is too wide or too tall is overlooked by some users and deliberately avoided by others — and excess content adds page weight and data cost.

          </div>
        
        
                  <div class="devsite-landing-row-item-buttons">
      <a href="/web/fundamentals/design-and-ux/responsive/content#viewport"
      class="wf-small-link
      "
            >Design content to work well across different viewport sizes</a>    <a href="/web/fundamentals/design-and-ux/responsive/content#redundant"
      class="wf-small-link
      "
            >Eliminate redundant content</a>    <a href="/web/fundamentals/design-and-ux/responsive/content#write"
      class="wf-small-link
      "
            >Write for mobile</a>    <a href="https://www.ampproject.org/"
      class="wf-small-link
      "
            >Consider AMP HTML</a></div>
              </div>
    </div>
      
</div>
              <div class="devsite-landing-row-item"
     
     >

  
    <div class="devsite-landing-row-item-media
            ">
      <figure class="devsite-landing-row-item-image">
          <img alt=""
       src="https://developers.google.com/web/billions/images/monetization.png"
       srcset="https://developers.google.com/web/billions/images/monetization_36.png 36w,https://developers.google.com/web/billions/images/monetization_48.png 48w,https://developers.google.com/web/billions/images/monetization_72.png 72w,https://developers.google.com/web/billions/images/monetization_96.png 96w,https://developers.google.com/web/billions/images/monetization_480.png 480w,https://developers.google.com/web/billions/images/monetization_720.png 720w,https://developers.google.com/web/billions/images/monetization_856.png 856w,https://developers.google.com/web/billions/images/monetization_960.png 960w,https://developers.google.com/web/billions/images/monetization_1440.png 1440w,https://developers.google.com/web/billions/images/monetization_1920.png 1920w,https://developers.google.com/web/billions/images/monetization_2880.png 2880w"
       sizes="(max-width: 840px) 50vw, 464px">
  
  </figure>
  </div>


        <div class="devsite-landing-row-item-description"
         >

      

      <div class="devsite-landing-row-item-body">
        
                    <h3 id="transactions-monetization-think-global">
      Transactions & monetization: think global</h3>
    
    

                  <div class="devsite-landing-row-item-description-content">
            Payment systems are inaccessible for many people on the web. Many users globally don't have bank accounts and don't use credit cards — including 8% of US households. Many payment systems don't work well on small viewports or with unreliable connectivity.

          </div>
        
        
                  <div class="devsite-landing-row-item-buttons">
      <a href="/web/fundamentals/design-and-ux/principles#commerce-and-conversion"
      class="wf-small-link
      "
            >Streamline transactions</a>    <a href="/web/fundamentals/design-and-ux/input/forms"
      class="wf-small-link
      "
            >Streamline forms</a>    <a href="/web/fundamentals/design-and-ux/principles#usability-and-form-factor"
      class="wf-small-link
      "
            >Design orientation-friendly layouts for small screens</a></div>
              </div>
    </div>
      
</div>
              <div class="devsite-landing-row-item"
     
     >

  
    <div class="devsite-landing-row-item-media
            ">
      <figure class="devsite-landing-row-item-image">
          <img alt=""
       src="https://developers.google.com/web/billions/images/localization.png"
       srcset="https://developers.google.com/web/billions/images/localization_36.png 36w,https://developers.google.com/web/billions/images/localization_48.png 48w,https://developers.google.com/web/billions/images/localization_72.png 72w,https://developers.google.com/web/billions/images/localization_96.png 96w,https://developers.google.com/web/billions/images/localization_480.png 480w,https://developers.google.com/web/billions/images/localization_720.png 720w,https://developers.google.com/web/billions/images/localization_856.png 856w,https://developers.google.com/web/billions/images/localization_960.png 960w,https://developers.google.com/web/billions/images/localization_1440.png 1440w,https://developers.google.com/web/billions/images/localization_1920.png 1920w,https://developers.google.com/web/billions/images/localization_2880.png 2880w"
       sizes="(max-width: 840px) 50vw, 464px">
  
  </figure>
  </div>


        <div class="devsite-landing-row-item-description"
         >

      

      <div class="devsite-landing-row-item-body">
        
                    <h3 id="plan-for-localization">
      Plan for localization</h3>
    
    

                  <div class="devsite-landing-row-item-description-content">
            Localization can help you access new markets. Many websites are only published in English, but English is not the first language of most people online. Only 5.52% of the world's population are native English speakers and US or European cultural conventions may not be familiar or intuitive. Instructions or prompts that are succinct and compact in English may be verbose and obtrusive in other languages.

          </div>
        
        
                  <div class="devsite-landing-row-item-buttons">
      <a href="https://support.google.com/webmasters/answer/182192/"
      class="wf-small-link
      "
            >Architect your site to enable localization</a></div>
              </div>
    </div>
      
</div>
